column4: Linguine are the long pasta par excellence: in the shape of small, flat and narrow tagliatelle, they were created to be served with the traditional pesto. Precisely thanks to the flat section and the slightly convex shape, they are perfect for soaking up sauces and giving them back the full flavor variety. They taste great simply with butter and sage, or with sauces based on tomatoes or vegetables and fresh herbs, and with quick, spicy sauces made with extra virgin olive oil, garlic, chili peppers, anchovies and capers. In addition, they are ideal with fish sauces with shellfish and seafood, as well as with light sauces made with milk cream, mascarpone, soft and processed cheese and with the addition of spices such as saffron, horseradish, , De Cecco GmbH has provided the above information.

column4: They come from the Campania region and belong to the family of particularly short, straight-cut pasta. In the past, fusilli were made by hand according to a method handed down from mother to daughter. A spaghetti had to be wrapped around a knitting needle particularly quickly and skilfully. The dexterity required for this activity is strongly reminiscent of spinning machines and the term "fusillo" actually comes from "fuso", the working instrument typical of spinning machines. They go well with both meat sauces and fish sauces, as well as sauces made with ricotta. They can also be served with vegetable sauces prepared with a tomato sauce and with the addition of peppers, aubergines, courgettes, olives and capers. , F.lli De Cecco di Filippo Fara S.Martino SpA has provided the above information.

column4: - 6 Pfanni bread dumplings in a practical cooking bag. - Bread with a particularly high, aromatic crust content and fine spices. - Quick and easy preparation. - Made from qualitative raw materials for an unmistakable taste. - Ideal for roasts, goulash and sauce dishes. The bread dumpling is simply the undisputed number one dumpling. The unmistakable dumpling taste according to Bavarian tradition makes a potato dish, roast pork, goulash and sauce dishes particularly delicious as a side dish. The hearty and spicy bread dumplings from Pfanni have long since crossed the borders of southern Germany as "Bavarian delicacies". The bread made from dumpling dough with a particularly high, aromatic crust and the finest spices give the bread dumpling its unmistakable taste. With Pfanni Semmel Dumplings in a cooking bag, you can quickly and easily prepare dumplings yourself, and the many different types of dumplings provide a tasty variety on the table. This is practical and delicious! This makes eating with the family a tasty experience that tastes good for young and old alike! Quick and easy to prepare: 1. Unpack: Place the bread dumpling in a large pot of cold, salted water and let it soak for 10 minutes. 2. Boiling: Boil the bread dumpling briefly until it is bubbly and then let it simmer for 10 minutes over a low heat. 3. Quench: Take the bread dumpling out of the pot and briefly quench under cold water. 4. Serving: Tear open the cooking bag by the tabs, serve and enjoy the dumplings. Bon appetit! For the production of the bread dumplings, Pfanni only uses raw materials that meet the high quality standards. This ensures that the delicious taste of the bread dumplings gets where it belongs: on the plate. , Unilever Deutschland GmbH hat die oben genannten Informationen zur Verfügung gestellt.
